other_tests.findings: Lobular, granulomatous pathologic picture consistent with erythema induratum. Biopsy specimens of annular plaques interpreted as showing granuloma annulare.
other_tests.changes_over_time: After 8 months, all lesions had healed. The annular lesions never recurred.

other_tests.findings: Positive for mycobacterial DNA in the leg biopsy tissue. Negative for Mycobacterium tuberculosis DNA in the annular lesions.
Patient had a positive tuberculin skin test.
